metadata.name: life is a (beautiful) mess #84
metadata.description:
when carefully applied, chaos brings things to life.

'life is a (beautiful) mess' was created as i led a certain amount of chaos take control of an animated textile algorithm i'm developing. 
as soon as it happened i realized that it was a great representation of our lives. 
each line represents one of us and the patterns that appear repeatedly are the situations we live which make us move, feel and be in a certain way. 
the image created is the sum of our paths in this life, as they only make sense when we look at them as one.

---

i hope you find it pleasant to watch this animation, how it develops and grows during aprox 1'30"
there are pieces drawn with the 4 typical school pen colors: black, green, blue and red. also a multicolor and a rare dark mode features.


press [s] to capture an image .png
press [r] to reload the animation
click the mouse to stop the animation
doubleclick the mouse to resume the animation

generative art created by mehno using p5js

metadata.name: Overgrowth #16
metadata.description:
This work is an exploration of random growth focused on three interconnected elements. The first is a randomly moving brush, the second is one is an alternating overlay of white and black circles along bezier points between brush movements, and the final one being a continually decreasing brush size.

The overall result gives a complex scribble art effect. 

Created with p5.js

metadata.name: Plottable Mountain Moons #3
metadata.description:
What makes this NFT have value? not only the digital is cool but it is the recipe to a plottable. Owning this NFT confers the right to request a physical plot (21cm square). @greweb will ask extra fees for this service => https://greweb.me/plots/nft

Full article: https://greweb.me/2021/12/plottable-mountain-moons

Plottable Mountain Moons generalize many explorations done this year. There are 13 inks, 9 different shape primitives with recursion, various intensity, and frequencies of noise,... and many rare cases to discover!

Digital and Physical art, hybrid and decoupled:
- The art is published via a digital NFT on Tezos blockchain – its digital representation simulates fountain pen inks drawing on paper with animated effects.
- Token to the physical world: owning each NFT confer the power to request the related physical plot: https://greweb.me/plots/nft

@greweb – 2021 – tech: WebGL + Rust + WASM – CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

metadata.name: patchwork #5
metadata.description:
Patchwork is a series combining shaders, tessellations and gradients to create new digital quilts woven together in a WebGL real time animation.

Each patch in the series comes with a different schema and variation, allowing the works to spread from maximalist marbling to meditative minimalism.

Each patch will bring a different digital quilt as an .html file to continuously move across the screen in a running loop.  (created w/ Koopero)

metadata.name: Butterfly Effect #4
metadata.description:
Well known is the butterfly effect, a system where it's not possible to predict how arbitrarily small changes in its initial conditions will affect the outcome.

This piece tries to achieve this with a few simple steps by manipulating uv-coordinates: rotate, distort, repeat n-times. Fitting the notion, the resulting images resemble butterflies. 

Btw, this is my genesis nft project.

To save a hi-res PNG (4096x4096 px), double click or hit 's' (give it a few seconds to generate).

metadata.name: Fält #20
metadata.description:
Fält is a study of shape, colour and texture. Designed to bring joy to the viewer, this is a work to light up the darkness of winter and awake feelings of curiosity. 

The series is controlled by a large number of random processes, from recursive subdivision with tweaks through Chaikin smoothing of the resulting polygons to mild domain warping of the entire canvas. Finally each shape is filled using small shapes, creating a warm and soft feel. 

Some features are tracked, but many are hidden in the resulting visuals, which will make exploration of the final collection surprising and rewarding.
